alert.note: Alert for San Luis Obispo; Santa Barbara (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued January 09 at 11:10PM PST until further notice by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...RIVER FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM PST TUESDAY FOR THE SISQUOC RIVER NEAR GAREY... * WHAT...River flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected in the Sisquoc River near Garey. * WHERE...A portion of southwest California, including the Sisquoc River in the following counties, San Luis Obispo and Santa Barbara. * WHEN...Until 1100 AM PST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Flooding of the Sisquoc River near Garey and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1105 PM PST, flooding along the Sisquoc River is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the warned area. Between 2 and 6 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts of 0.5 to 1.5 inches are possible in the warned area. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Stay away or be swept away. River banks and culverts can become unstable and unsafe.
